      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ADA TARO (1) was safely held last time out, finishing seventh at this track over 516m behind Zipping Augusta (31.97) in a Mix. Was a winner prior to that. Form from her last run is proving very strong. Has ability and looks hard to stop. KIANDO DIVA (8) has been in super consistent form, finishing in the minors at her last seven runs. Last start finished 3rd over 330m at Temora beaten 3.5 lengths (19.03) behind Let's Go Out in a Grade 5 on March 4. Leading player again. ITCHY'S FLYER (7) was in the minors two back (18.66) at this track but ran below best last time at Temora, finishing 7th. Solid record here at the distance winning two races. Strong form has emerged from her last run. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. FLASH GYPSY (2) should bounce back after an unplaced effort here recently.",
